  • Method Details

    • parseJSON

      public void parseJSON​(java.lang.String filePath)
      This method parses a JSON file located at the given file path and populates the 'connectors', 'portals', and 'players' JSONArray fields with the corresponding data from the file.
      Parameters:
      filePath - The path to the JSON file to parse

    • readConnectors

      public void readConnectors​(GameMap gameMap)
      This method reads the data from the 'connectors' JSONArray and creates Connector objects for each entry. The resulting Connector objects are stored in the 'connectorList' ArrayUnorderedList. Finally, the method prints the toString representation of each Connector in the 'connectorList'.

    • readPortals

      public void readPortals​(GameMap gameMap)
      Reads the portals from the JSON object and adds it to the portalList. Finally, the method prints the toString representation of each Portal in the 'portalList'

    • readPlayers

      public void readPlayers​(GameMap gameMap) throws PlayerWithNoTeamException
      Reads the players from the JSON object and adds it to the playerList. Finally, the method prints the data of each Player in the 'playerList' by using the 'showPlayerData()' method
      Throws:
      PlayerWithNoTeamException - if a player does not have a team specified.

    • readRoutes

      public void readRoutes()
      Reads the routes from the JSON object.
